{"cursor":"9916","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n]]\n\n'Nitrification' is the biological oxidation of ammonia with oxygen into nitrite\nfollowed by the oxidation of these nitrites into nitrates. Degradation of\nammonia to nitrite is usually the rate limiting step of nitrification.\nNitrification is an important step in the nitrogen cycle in soil. This process\nwas discovered by the Russian microbiologist, Sergei Winogradsky.\n","linknr":219,"url":"Nitrification","recorded":1362482282,"links":37,"instances":["soil"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Nitrogen metabolism","Soil biology"],"headings":["Microbiology and ecology","Chemistry","Nitrification in the marine environment","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Nitrogen_Cycle.svg/300px-Nitrogen_Cycle.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["mineralization","soil"]],"members":["mineralization"],"related":["Redox","Ammonia","Oxygen","Nitrite","Nitrite","Nitrate","Nitrogen_cycle","Soil","Russia","Microbiologist","Sergei_Winogradsky","Bacteria","Archaea","Î’-proteobacteria","Gammaproteobacteria","Chemotroph","Carbon_dioxide","Carbon","Calvin_Cycle","Nitrogen","Wastewater","Denitrification","Aeration","Methanol","Chloramines","Ammonification","Mineralization_(soil)","Nitrogen_cycle","Redox","Marine_environment","Limiting_nutrient","Nitrogen_cycle","Nitrate","F-ratio","Anthropogenic","Carbon_dioxide","PH","Ammonia","Oxidized","Nitrite","Ammonia_oxidizing_bacteria","Ammonia_monooxygenase","Metagenomic","Crenarchaeota","Archaea","Primary_production","Bacteria","Water_column